effeminate
	adj. (of a man) having or showing characteristics regarded as typical of a woman; unmanly
anachronistic
	adj. belonging to a period other than that being portrayed
sardonic
	adj. grimly mocking or cynical
salvo
	n. a simultaneous discharge of artillery or other guns in a battle
blithe
	adj. showing a casual and cheerful indifference considered to be callous or improper
sanguinary
	adj. involving or causing much bloodshed
ameliorate
	v. make (something bad or unsatisfactory) better
touchstone
	n. a standard or criterion by which something is judged or recognized
stanchion
	n. an upright bar, post, or frame forming a support or barrier
mendacious
	adj. not telling the truth; lying